ot Locker" |- | [[F. W. Woolworth Ireland]] | Europe | Retail | Spin-off | 1914–1984 | Former Irish division of F. W. Woolworth plc (later called [[Woolworths Group]]) |- | [[Kingfisher plc]] | Europe | Successor [[Parent company]] | Retailer | 1982–Present | Became Woolworth Holdings but then spun it off in 2001 |- | [[Ladybird (clothing)|Ladybird]] | Europe | Division Brand | Children's Clothing | 1938–Present | Now part of [[Shop Direct Group]] |- | [[Record Merchandisers Limited]] | Europe | [[Record Label]] | Division | 1966–1988 | Founded by [[EMI Records]] |- | [[Retail Company of Germany]] | Europe | [[Department store|Department]] | Division | 1927–1998 | German division that became Woolworth GmbH |- | [[Wellchester]] (originally Wellworths) | Europe | [[Stationery]] | Spin-off successor | 2009–2012 | 1 store in Dorchester |- | [[Woolworth GmbH]] | Europe | [[Department store|Department]] | Spin-Off | 1998–Present | Formerly Retail Company of Germany, founded in 1927 |- | [[Woolworths Group]] | Europe | Retail | Spin-off | 1909–2009 | Former British division |- | [[Woolworths (Cyprus)]] | Europe | [[Department store|Department]] | Division Spin-off | 1950s–2003 | Now a [[Debenhams]] franchise |- | [[Woolworths (Cyprus) Properties Public Limited|Woolworths (Cyprus) Properties]] | Europe | Retail Developer | Spin-off | 2005–Present | |- | [[Woolworths.co.uk]] | Europe | [[Online retailer]] | Spin-off successor | 2009–Present | Now part of [[Shop Direct Group]] |- | Runners Point | Europe | Athletic Clothing | Division | 2013–Present | German athletic stores acquired by Foot Locker in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footlocker-inc.com/investors.cfm?page=foot-locker-completes-rpg-acquisition}}</ref> |- style="background:orange" | colspan="6" | South African namesake |- | '''[[Woolworths (South Africa)]]''' | Africa | [[Department store|Department]] | Namesake | 1931–Present | Named after [[F. W. Woolworth Company|Woolworth's]] without any financial connect