{{Infobox software | name = Stride | logo = Stride (software) logo.svg | screenshot = | developer = [[Atlassian]] | latest_release_version = | latest_release_date = | latest_preview_version = | latest_preview_date = | operating_system = {{hlist | Mac | Linux | Windows | Android | iOS | web-based}} | genre = [[Business communication]] | license = [[Proprietary software|Proprietary]] | website = {{official URL}} }}
'''Stride''' was a [[Cloud computing|cloud]]-based team [[business communication]] and [[Collaborative software|collaboration tool]], launched by [[Atlassian]] on 7 September 2017 to replace the cloud-based version of [[HipChat]].<ref name="forbes">{{cite news|last=Weinberger |first=Matt |title=The chat wars are heating up as $8 billion Atlassian totally reinvents its app to take on Microsoft and Slack |url=http://www.businessinsider.com/atlassian-launches-hipchat-successor-stride-2017-9 |journal=Forbes |date=7 September 2017}}</ref> Stride software was available to download onto computers running [[Windows]], [[Mac OS|Mac]] or [[Linux]], as well as [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]] [[smartphones]], and [[Tablet computer|tablets]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Atlassian hopes to dent Slack's momentum with Stride, a new group collaboration tool|url=https://www.geekwire.com/2017/atlassian-hopes-dent-slacks-momentum-stride-new-group-collaboration-tool/|website=[[GeekWire]]|accessdate=22 September 2017|last=Krazit|first=Tom|date=7 September 2017}}</ref> Stride was bought by Atlassian's competitor [[Slack Technologies]] and will be discontinued on February 15th, 2019.<ref name="AtlassianSlackFAQ">{{cite web |url=https://www.atlassian.com/partnerships/slack/faq#faq-da2b66a1-53d3-4c4e-a405-467d961336f7 |title= Atlassian Slack FAQ |website=Atlassian |accessdate=20 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Atlassian’s HipChat and Stride to be discontinued, with Slack buying up the IP|publisher=TechCrunch|date=26 July 2018|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/07/26/atlassians-hipchat-and-stride-to-be-discontinued-with-slack-buying-up-the-ip/}}</ref>
The features of Stride include chat rooms, one-on-one messaging, file sharing, 5 GB of file storage, group voice and video calling, built-in collaboration tools, and up to 25,000 of searchable message history. Premium features include unlimited file storage, users, group chat rooms, file sharing and storage, apps, and history retention. The premium version, priced at $3/user/month, also includes advanced meeting functionality like group screen sharing, remote desktop control, and dial-in/dial-out capabilities. Stride offered integrations with Atlassian's other products as well as other third-party applications listed in the Atlassian Marketplace, such as [[GitHub]], [[Giphy]], Stand-Bot and [[Google Calendar]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Pricing that scales for your team's needs|publisher=Stride|date=22 August 2017|url=https://www.stride.com/pricing}}</ref>
Stride offered additional features beyond messaging to improve efficiency and productivity. It aimed to reduce collaboration noise by introducing a "focus" mode, and eliminates the divisions between text chat, voice meetings, and videoconferencing, by simplifying transitioning between these modes in the same channel.<ref name="forbes" /><ref>{{cite news |last=Dignan |first=Larry |title=Atlassian launches Stride, aims to curb 'over-collaboration,' noise in team communication |url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/atlassian-launches-stride-aims-to-curb-over-collaboration-noise-in-team-communication/ |website=ZDNet |date=7 September 2017}}</ref>
On July 26, 2018, [[Atlassian]] announced that HipChat and Stride would be discontinued February 15, 2019, and that it had reached a deal to sell their intellectual property to [[Slack (software)|Slack]].<ref name="AtlassianSlackFAQ" /> Slack will pay an undisclosed amount over three years to assume the user bases of the services, and Atlassian will take a minority investment in Slack. The companies also announced a commitment to work on integration of Slack with Atlassian services.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/7/26/17619482/slack-hipchat-acquisition-stride-atlassian-partnership-microsoft-teams-competition|title=Slack buys Hipchat with plans to shut it down and migrate users to its chat service|work=The Verge|access-date=2018-07-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techcrunch.com/2018/07/26/atlassians-hipchat-and-stride-to-be-discontinued-with-slack-buying-up-the-ip/|title=Slack is buying, and shutting down, HipChat and Stride|work=TechCrunch|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-US}}</ref>
